      Abstract:
        'This paper examines techniques for the model-based testing of web applications and multilingual websites. For this purpose, the simple web game application GuessNumbers is used to explain the essential steps for a model-based test process that applies statistical usage models to generate appropriate test suites. We also discuss methods for performing on-the-fly testing by means of an executable usage model. Model-based techniques that provide graphical representations of usage models make it easy to set the test focus on specific regions of the system under test that shall be tested. In addition, adapted profiles support the selective generation of test suites. We also show how generic usage models that are adapted to specific environments during the test execution, enable multilingual websites to be tested. Using the TestPlayer tool chain, a model-based testing approach is easily done. © 2019, Springer Nature Switzerland AG.',
