      Abstract:
        "As web applications are becoming more and more ubiquitous, modeling and testing web applications correctly is becoming necessary. In this paper, we have used a formal specification language, State chart to model the navigation behaviour aspect of web applications. This paper presents the ACT (Abstract to Concrete Tests) tool, an approach of generating concrete executable Selenium RC JUnit test cases from a formal State chart specification model. The ACT tool can generate concrete Selenium RC JUnit test cases from abstract test cases by utilizing data shared across different interactions of the web application with the web server. Throughout the paper, a case study of Learning Management System is used to illustrate our approach. Copyright © 2016 for the individual papers by the papers' authors.",
